WEBVTT

1
00:00:01.280 --> 00:00:02.919
Previously...

2
00:00:03.000 --> 00:00:05.080
You are what this town needs
for mayor.

3
00:00:05.160 --> 00:00:08.359
I know what I saw.
You and some woman.

4
00:00:08.439 --> 00:00:09.919
I think that you need to move out.

5
00:00:10.000 --> 00:00:12.895
You're using XK. aren't you? You lied to
me! I thought you were getting powers?

6
00:00:12.919 --> 00:00:14.679
It's not gonna happen again. okay?

7
00:00:14.759 --> 00:00:17.359
Timmy's mom found an inhaler.
Apparently. the police are involved.

8
00:00:17.440 --> 00:00:20.000
It's real. A different dimension.
A parallel universe.

9
00:00:20.079 --> 00:00:21.839
And if Ally's goal is to use
these pendants

10
00:00:21.920 --> 00:00:23.320
to become some kind of a God...

11
00:00:23.399 --> 00:00:25.495
Then I need to get it back
from Anderson and destroy it.

12
00:00:25.519 --> 00:00:28.879
An unidentified Kryptonian being
took the lives of two of our assets.

13
00:00:28.960 --> 00:00:31.640
Why didn't you tell me that thing
you were chasing was you?

14
00:00:31.719 --> 00:00:32.719
It's not me.

15
00:00:32.799 --> 00:00:34.280
You captured your doppelganger!

16
00:00:34.359 --> 00:00:36.399
I need to understand why he's here.

17
00:00:36.479 --> 00:00:39.719
You will find that pale son of a bitch
by any means necessary.

18
00:00:39.799 --> 00:00:43.000
or you will be stripped of your duties.

19
00:00:43.079 --> 00:00:46.079
Until he reveals the location
of that thing that killed our men.

20
00:00:46.159 --> 00:00:49.119
Superman will remain a prisoner
of the United States Government.

21
00:01:04.280 --> 00:01:06.480
Look what the wind blew in.

22
00:01:11.120 --> 00:01:12.120
What is this?

23
00:01:12.200 --> 00:01:14.879
Your jackbooted friends
brought you in last night.

24
00:01:15.680 --> 00:01:19.920
Or was it this morning?
Time loses all meaning in captivity.

25
00:01:21.519 --> 00:01:25.760
I wonder. brother. what you possibly
could have done to wind up here?

26
00:01:26.359 --> 00:01:29.096
Presumably. you've been on the rough
end of a rather vicious betrayal.

27
00:01:29.120 --> 00:01:30.519
Enough!

28
00:01:30.840 --> 00:01:32.920
I don't need to hear it
from you right now.

29
00:01:33.879 --> 00:01:35.879
There's been a misunderstanding.

30
00:01:37.959 --> 00:01:40.359
One I'm very anxious to hear about.

31
00:01:45.040 --> 00:01:46.359
Anderson.

32
00:01:54.640 --> 00:01:55.959
You need to let me out.

33
00:01:56.040 --> 00:01:57.560
Actually. I don't.

34
00:01:58.079 --> 00:02:00.680
I've been given full command
of this operation.

35
00:02:01.359 --> 00:02:04.200
Your arrest was sanctioned
by General Hardcastle herself.

36
00:02:04.560 --> 00:02:06.976
And given that you are actively
harboring a monster who killed

37
00:02:07.000 --> 00:02:09.216
American soldiers. I think the
consequences are appropriate.

38
00:02:09.240 --> 00:02:11.976
Once I destroy the pendant. I will bring
him in so he can stand trial.

39
00:02:12.000 --> 00:02:13.280
I don't care about a trial

40
00:02:13.639 --> 00:02:16.039
and I don't trust you
to keep your word.

41
00:02:17.039 --> 00:02:18.599
Tell me where he is.

42
00:02:21.080 --> 00:02:24.479
Fine. You can rot in here
with your brother.

43
00:02:27.199 --> 00:02:28.360
Anderson!

44
00:02:29.400 --> 00:02:30.919
There's a greater threat here.

45
00:02:31.000 --> 00:02:33.159
Her name is Ally Allston.
She's a cult leader.

46
00:02:33.680 --> 00:02:35.719
Whatever brought your suspect
to this world.

47
00:02:35.800 --> 00:02:37.280
she knows more about it
than anyone.

48
00:02:37.360 --> 00:02:39.879
She's dangerous
and she needs to be stopped.

49
00:02:39.960 --> 00:02:41.735
If you don't believe me.
then look into her yourself.

50
00:02:41.759 --> 00:02:45.080
Whoever this woman turns out to be.
it changes nothing.

51
00:02:45.879 --> 00:02:49.800
When I return. you will give me
the location of my suspect.

52
00:02:55.919 --> 00:02:58.479
Well. brother. now that we're alone.

53
00:02:58.560 --> 00:03:00.879
why don't you spin me a tale

54
00:03:00.960 --> 00:03:04.159
and tell me all about
this new monster you're after.

55
00:03:10.719 --> 00:03:14.639
SUPERMAN AND LOIS

56
00:03:15.639 --> 00:03:17.000
Clark is where?

57
00:03:17.639 --> 00:03:20.599
The same off-site prison
where I sent Tal-Rho.

58
00:03:21.759 --> 00:03:23.439
Is he being questioned or punished?

59
00:03:23.520 --> 00:03:25.080
And how long do they intend
to hold him?

60
00:03:25.120 --> 00:03:29.159
My contact didn't know. But they're
charging him with treason.

61
00:03:29.919 --> 00:03:32.080
Treason? That's insane.

62
00:03:32.159 --> 00:03:33.599
He's Superman for God's sake.

63
00:03:33.680 --> 00:03:35.280
Yes. I know. But here we are.

64
00:03:35.360 --> 00:03:38.199
And it doesn't sound like this is
gonna get resolved anytime soon.

65
00:03:38.280 --> 00:03:39.840
Well. then. I'll resolve it myself.

66
00:03:39.919 --> 00:03:41.719
Lois. you can't just barge into the DOD

67
00:03:41.800 --> 00:03:45.639
and demand Anderson release
Superman. Let me make some calls.

68
00:03:45.719 --> 00:03:47.879
Dad. you've been making calls
all night.

69
00:03:47.960 --> 00:03:50.120
We need to get him out of there.

70
00:03:51.280 --> 00:03:53.240
I'll head to the DOD.
raise a little noise.

71
00:03:53.319 --> 00:03:55.919
see if I can't get a face to face
with Hardcastle.

72
00:03:57.719 --> 00:03:58.919
Any updates on dad?

73
00:04:00.159 --> 00:04:01.879
Not yet. We're working on it.

74
00:04:05.120 --> 00:04:08.159
Why don't you write an article about
how Superman was taken to prison?

75
00:04:08.240 --> 00:04:10.319
Trust me. they would just deny it.

76
00:04:10.719 --> 00:04:13.479
You guys are gonna have to keep
yourselves busy after school. okay?

77
00:04:13.560 --> 00:04:15.800
Until your grandfather
and I figure this out.

78
00:04:15.879 --> 00:04:20.639
So whatever's going on between
you two. I suggest you figure it out.

79
00:04:23.160 --> 00:04:24.240
Jordan.

80
00:04:48.720 --> 00:04:50.560
This the last of dad's stuff?

81
00:04:50.639 --> 00:04:52.639
Honey. you shouldn't have to do that.

82
00:04:53.040 --> 00:04:54.800
I didn't want Sophie to see.

83
00:04:54.879 --> 00:04:57.000
I didn't want you to see.

84
00:04:57.600 --> 00:05:02.439
This is what's gotta happen. right?
Might as well just get it over with.

85
00:05:04.959 --> 00:05:08.879
I never wanted my daughters to know
what it felt like to have a broken home.

86
00:05:09.319 --> 00:05:10.839
Especially coming from one.

87
00:05:12.319 --> 00:05:15.120
I'm so sorry to put you
and your sister through this.

88
00:05:15.199 --> 00:05:17.480
Mom. you're not putting us anything.

89
00:05:18.279 --> 00:05:22.439
Dad is. None of this is your fault.

90
00:05:22.959 --> 00:05:25.439
None of it is yours. either. Okay?

91
00:05:28.560 --> 00:05:30.120
All right. honey. we gotta go.

92
00:05:30.199 --> 00:05:32.560
- Okay. I'll get Sophie ready.
- Thank you.

93
00:05:32.639 --> 00:05:34.240
Sophie! School!

94
00:05:47.439 --> 00:05:50.360
An evening with George Dean
The value of family values.

95
00:06:02.720 --> 00:06:05.199
- You going to first period?
- I don't know yet.

96
00:06:13.600 --> 00:06:15.199
You get any sleep last night?

97
00:06:15.279 --> 00:06:19.319
Not much. I just found out
my dad's moving out. so...

98
00:06:20.519 --> 00:06:22.720
- Like forever?
- Probably.

99
00:06:24.040 --> 00:06:27.600
- Well. maybe...
- I don't know. Jordan. Sorry.

100
00:06:28.199 --> 00:06:29.439
It's only been one night.

101
00:06:29.519 --> 00:06:32.439
and it's just so hard seeing my mom
cry all the time.

102
00:06:35.680 --> 00:06:36.959
I can imagine.

103
00:06:38.839 --> 00:06:40.759
I don't really know if you can.

104
00:06:52.639 --> 00:06:54.000
Hey. babe.

105
00:06:54.759 --> 00:06:57.759
Still thinking about
how sexy you were on the field.

106
00:06:57.839 --> 00:06:59.399
I did have a little help.

107
00:06:59.480 --> 00:07:01.360
Yeah. and it worked

108
00:07:02.399 --> 00:07:05.480
so I brought you some more.

109
00:07:07.800 --> 00:07:09.839
That should last you a while.

110
00:07:10.759 --> 00:07:11.759
Candice.

111
00:07:11.839 --> 00:07:16.120
- I'll hook you up with a good price.
- No. it's not about that.

112
00:07:19.120 --> 00:07:20.439
Honestly. I think I'm done.

113
00:07:20.519 --> 00:07:23.720
- Are you out of your mind?
- I can't. I can't do that anymore.

114
00:07:23.800 --> 00:07:25.680
Jon. you're starting quarterback. okay?

115
00:07:25.759 --> 00:07:28.519
You can't just stop.
This is what helped you get here.

116
00:07:28.600 --> 00:07:31.000
Everyone. I need you to step away
from your lockers.

117
00:07:31.079 --> 00:07:33.959
They're after of the X-K.

118
00:07:34.040 --> 00:07:36.360
I can't get caught with this stuff.
Jonathan.

119
00:07:36.439 --> 00:07:39.800
If the people my dad works for find out
about this. we're gonna lose everything.

120
00:07:39.879 --> 00:07:43.000
- No. you won't.
- What are you doing?

121
00:07:43.079 --> 00:07:45.839
I'll dump it. okay? I'm a good kid.

122
00:07:46.519 --> 00:07:49.040
No way they're gonna check me.
And if they do. then...

123
00:07:54.399 --> 00:07:57.480
No. dad. I will not hang tight
and let you do your thing.

124
00:07:58.839 --> 00:08:01.279
Well. then go to Hardcastle's office
and kick in the door.

125
00:08:01.360 --> 00:08:03.399
Because if you don't. I will.

126
00:08:04.519 --> 00:08:05.839
Fine. Call me back.

127
00:08:07.240 --> 00:08:09.399
Hey. Are you okay?

128
00:08:10.199 --> 00:08:14.360
Now Dean's acting like he's the family
values candidate? Seriously?

129
00:08:14.920 --> 00:08:16.160
I know. it's absurd.

130
00:08:16.600 --> 00:08:19.079
Yeah. that seems to be the strategy
they're going for.

131
00:08:19.160 --> 00:08:21.776
And unfortunately. his campaign can
print whatever message they want.

132
00:08:21.800 --> 00:08:25.040
I have to fight back.
How much did he pay for this?

133
00:08:26.279 --> 00:08:28.839
- Three thousand dollars.
- I can't afford that.

134
00:08:28.920 --> 00:08:32.120
If it was up to me. I would run
your ads for free every single day.

135
00:08:32.200 --> 00:08:33.799
up until the election.

136
00:08:34.399 --> 00:08:37.919
But I'm afraid that would violate every
campaign finance law imaginable.

137
00:08:38.000 --> 00:08:39.080
So would I do?

138
00:08:39.519 --> 00:08:41.480
Dean's got the power of his office

139
00:08:41.559 --> 00:08:44.120
and the town gossip
all working in his favor.

140
00:08:44.200 --> 00:08:47.399
But you have the truth.
Don't underestimate that.

141
00:08:47.480 --> 00:08:49.679
There's still plenty of time
to beat Dean.

142
00:08:49.759 --> 00:08:51.559
You just have to catch him off-guard.

143
00:08:53.960 --> 00:08:55.080
One sec.

144
00:08:57.519 --> 00:08:58.639
Hello?

145
00:09:02.120 --> 00:09:03.679
He was caught with what?

146
00:09:04.399 --> 00:09:05.639
I pity you. brother.

147
00:09:06.440 --> 00:09:10.000
I mean. after everything you've done
for humanity. to find yourself here.

148
00:09:10.080 --> 00:09:11.759
Do you ever stop talking?

149
00:09:11.840 --> 00:09:16.080
Cast out.
imprisoned. it's humiliating.

150
00:09:16.159 --> 00:09:18.559
Yes. but the real punishment
is having to listen to you.

151
00:09:18.639 --> 00:09:20.879
Now. that is unfair.
I am on your side.

152
00:09:21.440 --> 00:09:24.399
Have you so quickly forgotten the aid
I provided last time we met?

153
00:09:24.480 --> 00:09:26.000
You attacked my son.

154
00:09:26.960 --> 00:09:28.840
An overreaction. I admit.

155
00:09:28.919 --> 00:09:30.320
But no harm came of it.

156
00:09:30.720 --> 00:09:33.480
And did I not bring you face to face
with our mother?

157
00:09:33.919 --> 00:09:36.600
For that good deed alone I deserve
at least some gratitude.

158
00:09:36.679 --> 00:09:39.679
You got what you deserved.
to be locked up in here.

159
00:09:39.759 --> 00:09:41.279
With you.

160
00:09:41.840 --> 00:09:46.440
Last chance. Superman.
Where's my suspect?

161
00:09:46.519 --> 00:09:48.639
I asked you to look into Ally Allston.

162
00:09:48.720 --> 00:09:50.495
If you did. then you know
what we're up against.

163
00:09:50.519 --> 00:09:52.416
If you didn't. then I need to speak
to General Hardcastle.

164
00:09:52.440 --> 00:09:54.240
I told you. I'm in command now.

165
00:09:54.759 --> 00:09:56.759
And I want that thing
that killed my team.

166
00:09:57.120 --> 00:09:59.159
But if you won't tell me where he is.

167
00:10:00.960 --> 00:10:02.200
maybe he will.

168
00:10:02.960 --> 00:10:04.440
I beg your pardon?

169
00:10:07.440 --> 00:10:10.240
You Kryptonians must have
so many secrets.

170
00:10:11.080 --> 00:10:13.879
Maybe my suspect's hidey-hole
is among them.

171
00:10:15.720 --> 00:10:19.679
Assuming that were true. what
will you offer for my cooperation?

172
00:10:25.159 --> 00:10:27.399
That's simple. I'll make the pain stop.

173
00:10:29.200 --> 00:10:30.360
Stop!

174
00:10:37.759 --> 00:10:38.759
Hey.

175
00:10:39.240 --> 00:10:42.799
Do you know anything about Jonathan
Kent taking this drug from the mines?

176
00:10:43.960 --> 00:10:45.480
Can you let me
put my stuff down first?

177
00:10:45.559 --> 00:10:47.279
- Sarah. this is serious.
- I know.

178
00:10:47.360 --> 00:10:49.960
I was there when the sheriff came in.

179
00:10:50.759 --> 00:10:52.176
No. I didn't know anything about it.

180
00:10:52.200 --> 00:10:53.440
Thank God.

181
00:10:53.519 --> 00:10:55.519
Yeah. Jordan's freaking out.

182
00:10:56.000 --> 00:10:57.519
But please just promise me...

183
00:10:57.600 --> 00:11:00.879
Not to smoke space drugs?
Yeah. I'm not that stupid.

184
00:11:04.559 --> 00:11:05.559
What is it?

185
00:11:06.000 --> 00:11:08.840
It's just dad calling
for like the hundred time.

186
00:11:10.639 --> 00:11:12.399
- Are you okay?
- Yeah.

187
00:11:16.000 --> 00:11:19.600
No. I just feel like I can't talk
to Jordan about everything.

188
00:11:19.679 --> 00:11:22.759
I mean. he's sweet but the biggest
problem he has with his dad

189
00:11:22.840 --> 00:11:25.720
is the coach shorts
that Mr. Kent likes to wears.

190
00:11:25.799 --> 00:11:28.559
And he just has a lot going on
with his family right now.

191
00:11:28.639 --> 00:11:30.480
He doesn't need another thing.

192
00:11:31.279 --> 00:11:35.639
You know. it might be good for you
to just vent to a friend a little bit.

193
00:11:36.000 --> 00:11:39.559
Is there anyone else you feel
comfortable talking to you about this?

194
00:11:43.600 --> 00:11:45.840
Twenty X-K inhalers?

195
00:11:47.480 --> 00:11:48.639
Twenty!

196
00:11:48.720 --> 00:11:50.895
- I was getting rid of them.
- Do not lie to me. Jonathan!

197
00:11:50.919 --> 00:11:55.200
Not today. This family is going through
enough right now.

198
00:11:55.279 --> 00:11:59.919
And I am trying so hard
to keep it together.

199
00:12:00.519 --> 00:12:03.720
so I'm gonna ask you and
you're gonna be honest with me.

200
00:12:04.919 --> 00:12:08.080
- Are you selling drugs?
- No. mom. I promise.

201
00:12:08.639 --> 00:12:12.559
And it's not even technically drugs.
The sheriffs not even pressing charges.

202
00:12:12.639 --> 00:12:15.080
Tell that to the school. Jonathan.
They're meeting right now

203
00:12:15.159 --> 00:12:18.679
to decide whether or not
to have you expelled.

204
00:12:18.759 --> 00:12:23.000
And regardless of how you classify
"experimental space narcotics".

205
00:12:24.000 --> 00:12:26.360
what the hell were you doing
with so much of it?

206
00:12:30.559 --> 00:12:31.960
I can't tell you that.

207
00:12:32.039 --> 00:12:34.519
If you ever wanna leave
this house again. you better.

208
00:12:34.600 --> 00:12:37.519
- Mom. people are gonna get in trouble.
- Yeah. Drug dealers.

209
00:12:39.279 --> 00:12:42.399
Mom. I understand that you're upset.
But I cannot rat...

210
00:12:42.480 --> 00:12:45.120
Do you have any idea
how much trouble you are in?

211
00:12:45.720 --> 00:12:48.720
What. you just think. "my mom can
just talk my way out of this"?

212
00:12:48.799 --> 00:12:53.480
I am so pissed. And trust me.
Jonathan. your father will be. too.

213
00:12:56.360 --> 00:12:58.440
Were you involved with this?

214
00:13:00.720 --> 00:13:03.799
I found out the other night.

215
00:13:05.600 --> 00:13:07.080
The other night?

216
00:13:08.240 --> 00:13:10.600
Jordan caught me using X-K
and called me out.

217
00:13:10.679 --> 00:13:12.200
And I haven't used it since.

218
00:13:12.600 --> 00:13:14.879
So you were using this stuff?

219
00:13:18.720 --> 00:13:22.000
For the last couple of weeks. yeah.
'cause Timmy was using it

220
00:13:22.559 --> 00:13:25.279
and I didn't think
that I could beat him without.

221
00:13:27.720 --> 00:13:29.279
Who are you?

222
00:13:30.919 --> 00:13:32.200
You know what?

223
00:13:32.840 --> 00:13:37.279
I have had enough disappointment
for today.

224
00:13:38.039 --> 00:13:40.360
So get upstairs right now.
both of you.

225
00:13:50.639 --> 00:13:54.080
Tell me where he is before
the Kryptonite destroys you.

226
00:13:55.039 --> 00:13:57.480
Anderson. you don't understand
what you're asking me to do.

227
00:13:57.559 --> 00:14:00.159
That suspect has knowledge we may
need to stop something terrible.

228
00:14:00.240 --> 00:14:01.840
I don't care.

229
00:14:03.000 --> 00:14:04.519
You're willing to die for him?

230
00:14:05.039 --> 00:14:07.320
The man who put you here
in the first place?

231
00:14:07.960 --> 00:14:09.759
Brother. please.

232
00:14:09.840 --> 00:14:11.360
Enough!

233
00:14:11.440 --> 00:14:14.960
He's at 76.2 North longitude.
100.4 West latitude.

234
00:14:15.720 --> 00:14:17.159
Take it off!

235
00:14:20.240 --> 00:14:23.200
Thank you for your cooperation.

236
00:14:33.799 --> 00:14:39.320
Those coordinates are
to your Fortress in the Arctic.

237
00:14:39.919 --> 00:14:42.720
- That should keep him busy.
- For now.

238
00:14:42.799 --> 00:14:45.399
But when he returns.
he is going to kill me.

239
00:14:49.279 --> 00:14:52.279
What will you do then. brother?

240
00:14:58.360 --> 00:15:01.279
Hey. I am sorry to show up
out of nowhere.

241
00:15:01.360 --> 00:15:03.056
and I know how much
you're going through right now.

242
00:15:03.080 --> 00:15:04.559
but I really just need talk.

243
00:15:04.639 --> 00:15:05.879
Of course.

244
00:15:08.399 --> 00:15:11.519
Do you really think Jonathan
was selling X-K?

245
00:15:12.840 --> 00:15:15.375
He claims it wasn't his. but who
knows if he's telling the truth.

246
00:15:15.399 --> 00:15:18.519
He didn't admit he was using it until
after his brother outed him.

247
00:15:18.960 --> 00:15:21.720
It's awful. And what did Clark say?

248
00:15:22.279 --> 00:15:23.480
He doesn't know.

249
00:15:24.480 --> 00:15:27.600
I'm afraid that when he finds out.
he's never gonna forgive him.

250
00:15:27.960 --> 00:15:32.519
How did I miss this?
I had no idea this was going on.

251
00:15:32.879 --> 00:15:34.879
You cannot blame yourself.

252
00:15:35.639 --> 00:15:40.000
Kids that age are pretty good
at keeping secrets from their parents.

253
00:15:40.080 --> 00:15:41.200
I know.

254
00:15:42.759 --> 00:15:45.440
I just didn't know the boys had
these types of secrets.

255
00:15:47.840 --> 00:15:49.919
Why would he do something like that?

256
00:15:54.240 --> 00:15:58.360
You know.
after Sarah's suicide attempt.

257
00:15:59.159 --> 00:16:02.240
I kept wanting her to tell me
why she did it.

258
00:16:02.320 --> 00:16:05.519
Because that's what I needed to hear
to make myself feel better.

259
00:16:05.879 --> 00:16:08.279
But when we did finally talk about it.

260
00:16:08.840 --> 00:16:11.879
I realized that the best thing
I could do was just listen.

261
00:16:12.360 --> 00:16:15.519
Even if the answer
wasn't what I wanted to hear.

262
00:16:15.600 --> 00:16:19.200
it let her know that I was there
for her. no matter what.

263
00:16:19.799 --> 00:16:23.960
And sometimes that's the only job
as a mom.

264
00:16:25.000 --> 00:16:27.919
to be there for your kid.
when they don't have anyone else.

265
00:16:32.320 --> 00:16:34.600
I think that Mayor Dean made
a big mistake

266
00:16:34.679 --> 00:16:36.840
bringing up the family values.

267
00:16:37.559 --> 00:16:40.960
I'm pretty sure I still have a husband
that cheated on me.

268
00:16:41.039 --> 00:16:42.960
But you are a great mom.

269
00:16:43.559 --> 00:16:47.000
And accusing a good mom of being
a bad one is terrible politics.

270
00:16:50.000 --> 00:16:51.679
Yeah. You're right.

271
00:16:52.679 --> 00:16:56.000
I just need to call him out.
Take the fight to him.

272
00:16:57.399 --> 00:17:00.559
I am so sorry.
Are you okay?

273
00:17:01.559 --> 00:17:03.360
What?
Is that your supplier freaking out?

274
00:17:03.960 --> 00:17:05.079
Shut up!

275
00:17:05.160 --> 00:17:07.480
I wasn't the one selling drugs
to the football team so...

276
00:17:08.920 --> 00:17:11.720
For the last time.
I wasn't selling drugs!

277
00:17:11.799 --> 00:17:13.696
Okay. Then why'd you have
that bag full of all vials?

278
00:17:13.720 --> 00:17:15.559
Look. I thought
that I could get rid of it.

279
00:17:16.440 --> 00:17:19.039
Whatever. I thought that if I got
caught. it wasn't a big deal.

280
00:17:19.119 --> 00:17:21.799
- I thought I'd be in a little trouble.
- A little trouble?

281
00:17:21.880 --> 00:17:24.160
- Yes.
- Was there someone on the team?

282
00:17:24.240 --> 00:17:25.799
- Was it Wellnitz?
- No!

283
00:17:27.200 --> 00:17:28.359
Please. stop.

284
00:17:29.000 --> 00:17:31.376
I don't know why you'd get in all this
trouble if it was someone else's.

285
00:17:31.400 --> 00:17:33.640
Look. I made a dumb decision.
You were right.

286
00:17:33.720 --> 00:17:35.240
I'm a terrible brother.

287
00:17:36.160 --> 00:17:38.599
Now. can you please
just leave me alone?

288
00:17:40.839 --> 00:17:41.920
Yeah.

289
00:17:49.799 --> 00:17:51.480
You would let them torture me?

290
00:17:51.880 --> 00:17:54.599
I'm a prisoner here. Same as you.

291
00:17:55.039 --> 00:17:57.440
Yes. but you could secure
your own release.

292
00:17:58.279 --> 00:18:01.359
My fate here
is of a more permanent nature.

293
00:18:04.839 --> 00:18:06.119
Unless...

294
00:18:09.799 --> 00:18:10.799
Unless what?

295
00:18:11.240 --> 00:18:14.160
I happen to know
a few of your secrets. don't I?

296
00:18:15.240 --> 00:18:18.160
Delicate matters I might very well use
to my advantage.

297
00:18:18.240 --> 00:18:19.839
We are approaching the target.

298
00:18:19.920 --> 00:18:22.319
Proceed with caution.
If that thing is in there.

299
00:18:22.400 --> 00:18:23.400
it's extremely dangerous.

300
00:18:25.039 --> 00:18:26.720
It appears to be empty. sir.

301
00:18:27.759 --> 00:18:29.079
Damn it. He lied to me.

302
00:18:29.160 --> 00:18:30.359
Don't threaten me.

303
00:18:30.440 --> 00:18:34.039
You're not the one being brought to heel
by some barbarous Kryptonite collar.

304
00:18:34.119 --> 00:18:37.400
Perhaps. I might extend my leash by
shining a light on all your many lies.

305
00:18:37.480 --> 00:18:38.640
That's enough!

306
00:18:40.359 --> 00:18:42.799
Is it. brother? I think not.

307
00:18:43.599 --> 00:18:45.039
Sir. we found something.

308
00:18:47.799 --> 00:18:49.440
Any idea what this is?

309
00:18:49.519 --> 00:18:51.119
It's that thing's suit.

310
00:18:51.759 --> 00:18:54.000
Superman must have warned him
we were coming.

311
00:18:54.079 --> 00:18:55.200
They're working together.

312
00:18:55.279 --> 00:18:57.279
This whole time.
Superman's been lying to me.

313
00:18:57.359 --> 00:18:58.480
And there's the proof.

314
00:19:24.920 --> 00:19:26.279
Move. move. move!

315
00:19:27.000 --> 00:19:29.279
Prisoners. back away
from each other. Now!

316
00:19:30.000 --> 00:19:31.880
I gave you an order. Let him go!

317
00:19:32.839 --> 00:19:35.839
Prisoner! Back away or my soldiers
will open fire.

318
00:19:36.759 --> 00:19:38.960
Of course. My apologies.

319
00:19:39.920 --> 00:19:43.240
Sir. General Hardcastle's on line one.
Says she's been trying to reach you.

320
00:19:44.319 --> 00:19:46.480
Hold her off until we have something
to report.

321
00:19:48.440 --> 00:19:50.279
What the hell is going on in there?

322
00:19:53.519 --> 00:19:54.640
Is he breathing?

323
00:19:54.720 --> 00:19:56.359
He's Superman. I'm sure he's fine.

324
00:19:56.440 --> 00:19:57.680
Check his pulse. soldier.

325
00:19:58.079 --> 00:20:00.559
Those are Kryptonians.
Get the men out of that cell!

326
00:20:00.640 --> 00:20:01.640
Sir? Say it again?

327
00:20:01.720 --> 00:20:03.880
Do not approach the prisoner!
Fall back!

328
00:20:11.440 --> 00:20:13.160
- Don't shoot me.
- Tal!

329
00:20:13.240 --> 00:20:17.279
I played my part. you could at least
let me have a little fun.

330
00:20:26.359 --> 00:20:28.079
I've missed this feeling.

331
00:20:30.839 --> 00:20:32.680
Look. here comes the cavalry.

332
00:20:33.279 --> 00:20:34.880
I'll take that as my cue.

333
00:20:47.759 --> 00:20:49.799
Satellite has prisoners
on course for the Badlands.

334
00:20:49.880 --> 00:20:51.255
That's where Superman fought
Tal-Rho.

335
00:20:51.279 --> 00:20:53.335
You really believe they've been
working together this whole time?

336
00:20:53.359 --> 00:20:56.680
We have to presume
that everything is part of some plot.

337
00:20:56.759 --> 00:20:59.400
Good luck getting the brass
to give a damn. I need a chopper.

338
00:20:59.480 --> 00:21:00.839
But sir. General Hardcastle.

339
00:21:00.920 --> 00:21:03.319
She's gonna take away my command
if I don't prove I'm right.

340
00:21:03.400 --> 00:21:05.160
The best way to do that
is to finish this.

341
00:21:07.960 --> 00:21:09.400
What are you gonna do?

342
00:21:10.480 --> 00:21:11.920
Simple.

343
00:21:14.319 --> 00:21:17.279
I'm gonna kill the bad guys
and bring Superman back.

344
00:21:19.640 --> 00:21:20.759
One way or another.

345
00:21:26.000 --> 00:21:29.400
Tal claims the two of you escaped
a prison and have joined forces.

346
00:21:31.200 --> 00:21:33.279
- I had no other choice.
- It was glorious. mother.

347
00:21:33.359 --> 00:21:36.319
Two sons of Krypton vanquishing
their human oppressors.

348
00:21:36.400 --> 00:21:37.920
you'd have been proud.

349
00:21:38.559 --> 00:21:43.039
It's fascinating. He's like some
warped version of you.

350
00:21:47.720 --> 00:21:49.160
And he babbles like an idiot.

351
00:21:49.240 --> 00:21:52.079
His words flow backwards.
unless...

352
00:21:54.039 --> 00:21:55.960
This man betrayed my family.

353
00:21:56.279 --> 00:21:57.559
Sounds familiar.

354
00:21:58.079 --> 00:21:59.495
I'm sure there's more to it than that.

355
00:21:59.519 --> 00:22:01.799
Were we always at odds
on your world?

356
00:22:01.880 --> 00:22:04.960
No. we were inseparable.

357
00:22:06.319 --> 00:22:07.680
the closest of brothers.

358
00:22:08.279 --> 00:22:11.079
What drove us apart?
Greed? Power?

359
00:22:12.240 --> 00:22:14.720
Your wife tried to kill me.

360
00:22:15.480 --> 00:22:16.680
My wife?

361
00:22:19.319 --> 00:22:20.319
My wife?

362
00:22:28.160 --> 00:22:30.039
Aubrey. hey.

363
00:22:36.200 --> 00:22:38.680
Thanks for coming.
I know that it's a long way.

364
00:22:39.160 --> 00:22:42.319
Wasn't that bad.
Clover's only like a two hour drive.

365
00:22:45.319 --> 00:22:48.759
So I know that I shouldn't have
ghosted you after camp.

366
00:22:50.519 --> 00:22:52.440
I get it. You have a boyfriend

367
00:22:52.519 --> 00:22:54.319
and you didn't want
to make it all weird.

368
00:22:54.759 --> 00:22:57.400
Yeah. but that doesn't mean
that it wasn't rude.

369
00:22:59.359 --> 00:23:01.079
I just wanted to say I'm sorry.

370
00:23:01.160 --> 00:23:04.440
Okay. Well. apology accepted.

371
00:23:06.680 --> 00:23:10.319
But that's not the only reason
why you texted me.

372
00:23:11.000 --> 00:23:15.400
Well. my life is falling apart.

373
00:23:16.400 --> 00:23:18.359
My dad cheated on my mom

374
00:23:18.440 --> 00:23:21.160
and I feel like you're the only person
who might understand.

375
00:23:23.559 --> 00:23:24.799
Okay.

376
00:23:24.880 --> 00:23:28.359
Well. child of divorce to the rescue.

377
00:23:29.079 --> 00:23:31.240
Just so you know.
I am like totally here for you.

378
00:23:31.319 --> 00:23:34.480
but can we please order form fries?
Because I'm literally starving.

379
00:23:38.599 --> 00:23:41.759
And now he won't just stop calling.

380
00:23:41.839 --> 00:23:43.160
Do you want to talk to him?

381
00:23:43.920 --> 00:23:45.279
No.

382
00:23:46.640 --> 00:23:50.119
Kind of. I mean.
it just doesn't seem fair to my mom.

383
00:23:50.559 --> 00:23:52.440
It's not about her. It's about you.

384
00:23:52.920 --> 00:23:56.880
After my parents split. I froze my dad
out for like almost an entire year

385
00:23:56.960 --> 00:23:59.079
and you know what?
It didn't fix their marriage.

386
00:23:59.160 --> 00:24:00.480
It didn't make me feel any better

387
00:24:00.519 --> 00:24:03.359
and if anything.
it just make me angry and mean.

388
00:24:03.680 --> 00:24:05.279
You? Mean?

389
00:24:05.880 --> 00:24:07.960
I got into like two fights that year.

390
00:24:08.039 --> 00:24:10.559
I actually chipped my front tooth.
It was so stupid.

391
00:24:10.640 --> 00:24:12.720
That's insane.

392
00:24:13.200 --> 00:24:14.759
So maybe spare your teeth.

393
00:24:14.839 --> 00:24:18.279
and if you want to see your dad.
see your dad.

394
00:24:20.519 --> 00:24:21.920
You're right.

395
00:24:22.680 --> 00:24:23.799
You're awesome.

396
00:24:24.240 --> 00:24:26.400
- I'm gonna hold you to that.
- Shut up.

397
00:24:29.079 --> 00:24:32.480
It's also later than I thought.
so I should probably get going.

398
00:24:33.480 --> 00:24:34.799
I got it.

399
00:24:40.000 --> 00:24:45.000
I was wondering maybe
we could be friends again.

400
00:24:48.920 --> 00:24:51.000
I was hoping you'd say that.

401
00:24:53.920 --> 00:24:55.200
- Bye.
- Bye.

402
00:25:23.480 --> 00:25:24.880
What now?

403
00:25:24.960 --> 00:25:27.359
I just wanted to say I'm sorry
about what happened.

404
00:25:28.680 --> 00:25:30.880
Okay. Well. thank you for saying that.

405
00:25:30.960 --> 00:25:33.279
And also I don't think
it was Jon selling those drugs.

406
00:25:33.720 --> 00:25:35.936
I know he was carrying them.
but you've got to believe me.

407
00:25:35.960 --> 00:25:38.079
I think he was just trying
to cover for someone else.

408
00:25:38.160 --> 00:25:39.519
I hope you're right.

409
00:25:40.480 --> 00:25:42.960
But you're still in trouble
for knowing about this.

410
00:25:58.480 --> 00:26:00.839
Let's try this again from the beginning.

411
00:26:03.640 --> 00:26:04.880
Okay.

412
00:26:07.559 --> 00:26:09.759
I found out
that Timmy was taking X-K.

413
00:26:09.839 --> 00:26:14.720
and so I got some and I started
taking it to keep up with him.

414
00:26:15.119 --> 00:26:17.319
You're right. it was just really stupid.

415
00:26:17.400 --> 00:26:20.400
But I really wanted to start
this season

416
00:26:21.319 --> 00:26:23.519
after everything that happened
last year.

417
00:26:24.319 --> 00:26:27.839
I feel like everybody in this family
is great at something

418
00:26:31.279 --> 00:26:33.759
and I wanted to be great I guess.

419
00:26:34.680 --> 00:26:38.519
It doesn't justify what I did.
not at all. But it's the truth.

420
00:26:39.759 --> 00:26:42.359
And just so you know.
I would never sell drugs.

421
00:26:43.240 --> 00:26:45.279
I believe you. sweetie. I do.

422
00:26:48.880 --> 00:26:51.200
But I'm still incredibly disappointed
in you.

423
00:26:51.640 --> 00:26:55.079
And taking drugs like that is just
something I never even thought

424
00:26:55.160 --> 00:26:56.759
you would consider doing.

425
00:26:57.559 --> 00:26:58.839
I will make it up to you.

426
00:26:59.279 --> 00:27:00.559
Okay? I promise.

427
00:27:01.200 --> 00:27:03.839
Then start by telling me
where you got the X-K.

428
00:27:06.640 --> 00:27:09.559
Jon. Principal Balcomb called me again
on the way back

429
00:27:09.640 --> 00:27:12.720
and unless you can prove
that those inhalers were not yours.

430
00:27:12.799 --> 00:27:15.119
the school board is gonna expel you.

431
00:27:16.680 --> 00:27:18.839
I can't ruin someone else's life.

432
00:27:20.119 --> 00:27:21.279
What about your life?

433
00:27:22.039 --> 00:27:24.920
Honey. I know that you think that
what you are doing is right.

434
00:27:25.000 --> 00:27:28.200
but sometimes in life. there are
mistakes that we cannot take back.

435
00:27:28.279 --> 00:27:30.599
And I assure you this is one of them.

436
00:27:33.880 --> 00:27:35.559
Please. just tell me.

437
00:27:37.799 --> 00:27:39.119
I'm sorry.

438
00:27:42.680 --> 00:27:43.839
So am I.

439
00:27:45.039 --> 00:27:49.119
I can't stop thinking that I had a wife.
She must be a goddess.

440
00:27:49.680 --> 00:27:51.480
Any idea where I might find her
on this earth?

441
00:27:51.519 --> 00:27:52.880
Can we please focus?

442
00:27:52.960 --> 00:27:55.839
At least. let him tell me her name.
How long is that gonna take?

443
00:27:57.079 --> 00:27:58.440
Something is coming.

444
00:28:00.400 --> 00:28:01.720
It's a missile.

445
00:28:20.279 --> 00:28:21.839
Superman!

446
00:28:23.440 --> 00:28:25.480
You will stand down or I will open fire.

447
00:28:26.160 --> 00:28:29.000
- You don't have to do this.
- I'm bringing you in.

448
00:28:29.079 --> 00:28:31.759
All of you. By any means necessary.

449
00:28:44.599 --> 00:28:45.720
You!

450
00:28:47.839 --> 00:28:49.440
You killed my team.

451
00:28:49.519 --> 00:28:51.400
I kill anyone who gets in my way.

452
00:29:06.599 --> 00:29:07.920
Let him out of the cage.

453
00:29:08.680 --> 00:29:10.240
I'm not gonna do that.

454
00:29:10.920 --> 00:29:12.359
Fine.

455
00:29:13.440 --> 00:29:15.279
I'll get him out of there myself.

456
00:29:17.160 --> 00:29:19.640
I don't appreciate intruders
in my home.

457
00:29:44.680 --> 00:29:45.920
Tal!

458
00:29:48.480 --> 00:29:49.960
Help my sons.

459
00:30:14.799 --> 00:30:16.000
What?

460
00:30:16.960 --> 00:30:18.279
Now you suffer!

461
00:30:21.400 --> 00:30:22.599
Mother!

462
00:30:26.960 --> 00:30:29.960
Kryptonite fragments have pierced
several of his vital organs.

463
00:30:31.680 --> 00:30:33.039
You must disintegrate them.

464
00:30:54.680 --> 00:30:57.519
Be precise Kal or you will kill him.

465
00:31:14.599 --> 00:31:17.160
You did it. The kryptonite fragments
are destroyed.

466
00:31:18.160 --> 00:31:19.640
No. no. he's not healing.

467
00:31:19.720 --> 00:31:21.560
All that time in prison.
under the solar lamps.

468
00:31:21.799 --> 00:31:23.160
He needs the sun.

469
00:33:46.640 --> 00:33:49.880
I see you brought me back
to my proper place.

470
00:33:51.400 --> 00:33:53.319
You knew I could never let you go free.

471
00:33:53.400 --> 00:33:56.160
What a shame. We could've
conquered the world by now.

472
00:33:58.880 --> 00:34:01.200
You should get better
in a couple of days.

473
00:34:03.839 --> 00:34:07.839
My father used to say pain was just
a way of reminding me I was alive.

474
00:34:10.079 --> 00:34:11.599
Quite the gem.

475
00:34:14.400 --> 00:34:15.599
And you?

476
00:34:15.679 --> 00:34:19.400
Am I to assume your
misunderstanding with the humans

477
00:34:19.480 --> 00:34:20.840
has been resolved?

478
00:34:21.760 --> 00:34:22.960
More or less.

479
00:34:24.719 --> 00:34:27.480
They will no doubt apologize
for their oversteps

480
00:34:27.559 --> 00:34:29.840
and you will go back to trusting them.

481
00:34:30.920 --> 00:34:32.280
And Anderson?

482
00:34:32.760 --> 00:34:35.639
Escaped. But I'll find him.

483
00:34:36.639 --> 00:34:38.159
What of the other you?

484
00:34:41.159 --> 00:34:42.320
He's dead.

485
00:34:44.280 --> 00:34:45.840
Could've been me tonight.

486
00:34:46.440 --> 00:34:48.199
If you hadn't done what you did.

487
00:34:48.280 --> 00:34:49.960
What are brothers for?

488
00:34:53.840 --> 00:34:55.039
Thank you.

489
00:35:03.360 --> 00:35:04.599
Kal.

490
00:35:08.440 --> 00:35:09.920
Tell your son I'm sorry.

491
00:35:13.480 --> 00:35:16.559
Maybe someday.
you can tell him yourself.

492
00:35:18.239 --> 00:35:19.679
brother.

493
00:35:40.400 --> 00:35:42.960
A warrant has been issued
for Anderson's arrest.

494
00:35:43.039 --> 00:35:45.599
He went AWOL.
stole government property.

495
00:35:46.079 --> 00:35:50.440
weapons from project 7734.
vials of confiscated X-K.

496
00:35:50.519 --> 00:35:53.280
And he blames Superman
for ruining his life and career.

497
00:35:53.360 --> 00:35:55.599
The sooner we get him behind bars.
the better.

498
00:35:56.760 --> 00:35:59.719
I want you to know. I offered
to lead the manhunt myself.

499
00:36:00.239 --> 00:36:02.400
It's not your responsibility. dad.
You're retired.

500
00:36:02.480 --> 00:36:06.360
Yeah. But I'm the one
who recommended him for the job.

501
00:36:21.719 --> 00:36:22.880
Long day.

502
00:36:24.079 --> 00:36:25.400
Long day.

503
00:36:25.960 --> 00:36:30.480
Sam. All I want now
is some Chinese food.

504
00:36:32.559 --> 00:36:34.239
a glass of red wine.

505
00:36:35.920 --> 00:36:37.039
and be with my family.

506
00:36:39.800 --> 00:36:40.840
What?

507
00:36:40.920 --> 00:36:43.599
You've always got to know
what's going on in your family.

508
00:36:43.679 --> 00:36:47.639
Because that's what this town is.
We are all family.

509
00:36:48.760 --> 00:36:52.559
Hell. Chuck and I went
to St. John Vianney together

510
00:36:52.639 --> 00:36:54.159
since first grade.

511
00:36:54.239 --> 00:36:58.880
Aidy. we sing next to each other
every Sunday in the choir.

512
00:36:58.960 --> 00:37:00.400
Now. let's be honest.

513
00:37:01.280 --> 00:37:04.559
Aidy's beautiful voice drowns me out.
but I'm trying.

514
00:37:05.639 --> 00:37:07.079
I'm trying.

515
00:37:07.639 --> 00:37:11.880
My point is this. if you can't keep
control of your own family.

516
00:37:12.639 --> 00:37:15.239
if you don't really know what's
going on in your own home.

517
00:37:15.840 --> 00:37:18.960
how are we to trust that you'd know
what's going on with all of us?

518
00:37:19.039 --> 00:37:23.360
Because I love this town. George.
And everyone in it.

519
00:37:23.960 --> 00:37:25.199
Well. Lana.

520
00:37:25.559 --> 00:37:31.320
I just can't be sure given your current
situation if we can be sure of that.

521
00:37:31.400 --> 00:37:34.880
I guess. I'll just have to make it clear
to everybody during our debates.

522
00:37:34.960 --> 00:37:37.800
But what should be really in question
here. George.

523
00:37:37.880 --> 00:37:39.639
is what kind of person you are.

524
00:37:40.039 --> 00:37:45.400
Someone so willing to attack
a member of this family

525
00:37:46.880 --> 00:37:49.519
during one of the most painful
moments of their life.

526
00:37:53.760 --> 00:37:56.159
Does that sound
like family values to you?

527
00:38:16.000 --> 00:38:17.320
Dad?

528
00:38:22.239 --> 00:38:23.400
Can we talk?

529
00:38:25.880 --> 00:38:27.039
Yeah.

530
00:38:35.840 --> 00:38:37.000
- You're back.
- Yeah. I am.

531
00:38:37.079 --> 00:38:39.439
I was not expecting to hear
what you're mother just told me.

532
00:38:39.480 --> 00:38:41.360
- Dad. I can explain.
- Jonathan. no.

533
00:38:41.920 --> 00:38:44.376
You're mom gave you multiple
chances to tell her the whole story.

534
00:38:44.400 --> 00:38:46.000
but you choose not to.

535
00:38:46.679 --> 00:38:48.679
- I'm sorry.
- What were you thinking?

536
00:38:49.400 --> 00:38:51.519
I wanted to be better.

537
00:38:51.599 --> 00:38:54.639
By taking drugs?
Have we thought you nothing?

538
00:38:54.719 --> 00:38:58.199
Have you not heard a single word that
either of us has ever said to you?

539
00:38:58.280 --> 00:39:00.480
- Yes.
- Then. damn. it. act like it.

540
00:39:03.039 --> 00:39:06.119
Tomorrow you will go and you will
apologize to Principal Balcomb.

541
00:39:06.199 --> 00:39:07.719
then you will apologize
to Coach Gaines

542
00:39:07.800 --> 00:39:10.240
and after that you will apologize
to the entire football team.

543
00:39:10.320 --> 00:39:12.776
Your mother and I are going to figure
out how you're going to finish

544
00:39:12.800 --> 00:39:14.119
the school year.

545
00:39:14.519 --> 00:39:17.239
whether it is in the next town over.
online. or somewhere else.

546
00:39:17.800 --> 00:39:19.599
And after all that. Jonathan.

547
00:39:20.079 --> 00:39:23.119
you and I are gonna have a long talk
about all the important things

548
00:39:23.199 --> 00:39:24.880
I though you already knew.

549
00:39:24.960 --> 00:39:29.079
so that you don't ever misrepresent
yourself or this family again.

550
00:39:30.079 --> 00:39:31.519
Do you understand?

551
00:39:31.920 --> 00:39:33.000
Yes. sir.

552
00:39:52.719 --> 00:39:54.000
Ally Allston.

553
00:39:57.119 --> 00:39:58.320
Yes?

554
00:39:58.960 --> 00:40:00.280
I'm Mitchell Anderson.

555
00:40:00.960 --> 00:40:03.599
Formerly of the United States
Department of Defense.

556
00:40:04.239 --> 00:40:06.920
I heard about you from Superman.

557
00:40:08.960 --> 00:40:10.280
From Superman?

558
00:40:10.719 --> 00:40:13.880
He thought you were dangerous
enough that I should look into you.

559
00:40:14.960 --> 00:40:19.199
And I have something that he wants.
but I think it belongs to you.

560
00:40:20.559 --> 00:40:21.960
Can you...

561
00:40:24.239 --> 00:40:26.199
Can you tell me what this is?

562
00:40:31.599 --> 00:40:32.880
That...

563
00:40:34.599 --> 00:40:36.920
That is the way to change to worlds.
